HEADWORD: Colorimeter
<hw>Col`or*im"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Color</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>colorim⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for measuring
the depth of the color of anything, especially of a liquid, by
comparison with a standard liquid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Colorimetry</ent>⟦br⟧
